1 d. Monitor the implementation of a response approved under section 23 - 27.2 - 04 ;
2 e. Monitor the implementation of a plan approved under section 23 - 27.2 - 06; and
3 f. Annually evaluate issued waivers.
4 3. The department may:
5 a. Issue waivers; and
6 b. Suspend or revoke a distressed ambulance service's license in accordance with
7 section 23 - 27.2 - 06 .
8 23-27.2-03. Licensee evaluation - Notice .
9 1. The department shall identify and evaluate licensees that have:
10 a. Failed to comply with federal or state law or regulation;
11 b. Indicated an intention to cease operation or change licensure level within sixty
12 days; or
13 c. Indicated a substantial likelihood of failure to respond to requests for service.
14 2. Upon identification of a licensee that meets the criteria under subsection 1, the
15 department may provide notice, in accordance with subsection 3, to the licensee by
16 first-class mail. If provided, the notice must be sent to the:
17 a. Licensee;
18 b. Service leader of record;
19 c. Medical director of record; and
20 d. Political subdivision that has jurisdiction over the licensee, if applicable.
21 3. The notice must include:
22 a. The deadline for the licensee to respond in accordance with section 23 - 27.2 - 04 ;
23 b. If the licensee failed to comply with federal or state law or regulation, the law or
24 regulation violated;
25 c. A detailed description of the violation or noncompliance;
26 d. The corrective action that must be taken by the licensee; and
27 e. Any resources available to the licensee to assist in taking corrective action.
28 23-27.2-04. Licensee - Response .
29 1. A licensee that receives a notice under section 23 - 27.2 - 03 shall respond to the
30 department within forty-five days of the date of the notice. The response must include:
